She meant everything to me and more. Even though we were long distance, we were so intimate, shared everything with each other. But a lot changed in a small period of time. We got into an argument, and wanting to be right got the better of me, my words hurt the only person I ever truly cared about; my sweetheart of over 3 years, nearing 4. I tried fixing it, fixing us, but she changed, I broke something inside of her. Het sweetness, her innocence, it seemed like it had all just disappeared. She was being short with me, which she never was before. We cried together, we went through a lot together, but I thoroughly believed we'd come out of this together, stronger than ever before. For a brief moment everything seemed to get better. I started to believe again, to have hope we'd get through this. We spoke of a house of our own, a brief glipse of a future, together. She told me she wanted to bring her teddybears, which made me smile. It reminded me of her innocence. It told me that somewhere inside, the girl I knew was still in there. One day she vanished, the night before she asked if we could go to bed, I was recovering from a surgery at that time. I wasn't really tired but for her I, I told her alright, because she hadn't been sleeping well lately, I thought she needed to rest as well. The day after I waited for her, all day. Days turned into weeks, weeks turned into months, months turned into almost a year. My sweetheart has left me, with worries, with doubts, with questions, but most importantly without goodbye. The questions still haunt me. Why? Why did you leave without saying goodbye? Why did you leave me on my own? Did you not see any other way out for us? Was all of it, everything we talked about, day and night, just a lie? Yesterday I saw her again, for a brief moment. She was playing a game, I joined one of her friends hoping to find her in there, and I did. Saw her running happilly after this other guy, when she saw me, she froze in place... and left. My heart has been torn out, I don't know how else I could describe this feeling, this gutwrenching feeling. I thought that with time, the pain would fade, it didn't, it only got worse. Why did I go looking for her? Has she already moved on from me? Did she forget about me? The thought of her being with someone other than me, it haunts me. A year ago I confessed this fear to her when we went through it all. She reassured me, told me that she doesn't want a new relationship; with anyone. I just wish she'd talk to me one more time, tell me that she was okay, even if it was something as simple as "Hi". She meant the world to me, and still does. I don't think i'll ever be able to move on from her. I never loved someone the way I loved her. It was real, and I know it was the same for her as well. I feel so alone, so empty, I lost my sense of purpose in life, and it hurts, so much...
